  "text": "A recent review of clinical trials employing perinatal tissue-derived products in advanced cell therapy identified 281 clinical studies registered between 2005 and 2015, and acquired neurological conditions or disorders was the second most common category of diagnosis behind trials in hematology or oncology with manipulated cell types [CITATION_1] . Of more than 500 cord blood units released for clinical application from our institution, 80% have gone to clinical trials or experimental uses in regenerative medicine, with the vast majority of those indications being neurological injuries sustained at or around the time of birth or diagnosis associated with said injuries (Figure 2 ).",
